Man That Was A Lot of Fun
•
•
•
Thank you to @thebrandoncolon the @project91events team and @versanyc for having myself and @jasonshapiro for our sunset B2B this past Saturday.

The whole reason I started DJing was because I went to a show and saw two incredibly talented DJs go B2B and have what looked like the most fun I’d ever seen and I’m happy to report…It was an absolute blast 

Special thanks to all who came out and danced with us.

Additionally, thank you to @dead.jed.lasso for the shots - if you think he took your picture reach out to him.

Until Next Time…

Say It 🗣️

Success…
•
•
•
Never in a million years when I made an offhand comment to @claptone.official in Jan 2022 after his show in Tulum that “maybe the next time I see you I’ll be on the other side DJing” did I think that it would happen.

Thank you to @project91events and @summerclubnyc for having me close for one of my favorite artists

Special Thank you to Claptone for coming back on after his set to join me to end the night by ripping Just A Ghost (@vintageculture remix) with me, and for the “one more song“ chant

More importantly thank you to everyone who came out partied like it was a Saturday and stayed to dance late late late into a Sunday night with us.

I’m not sure how I’m ever going to top this but until then… 

Be Good To Each Other

The recording should be up on SoundCloud tomorrow just in time for the long weekend.

Thanks to my makeshift media team of 
@alecsikar @thebrandoncolon @asherhbaron @joshschupak @isthisbridget @thedoncarta @genesiseventsny

Having an artist like @claptone.official chant one more song at the end of my set is the highest praise I’ve ever received…What A Life

Be Good To Each Other

•

Excited to be joining the line up for the @9andup.group Halloween Party at @wburghotel on Friday 10.27.23

Tickets last year were selling after market for 3x face - and while that is not encouraged it is indicative of how desirable this event was last year and will be this year 

There will be three different stages each with their own unique concept.

So unlike other venues you’ll be able to move around and explore without feeling  stuck in one location.

Oh yea and the first hour is open bar
